Well, the fact that I'm the owner.

1039
02:05:40,680 --> 02:05:41,520
What are you talking about?

1040
02:05:42,260 --> 02:05:43,810
The company went public a week ago.

1041
02:05:43,810 --> 02:05:45,680
And I bought most of the shares.

1042
02:05:46,220 --> 02:05:49,140
Through various charitable foundations and trusts and so forth.

1043
02:05:49,240 --> 02:05:55,000
Look, it's all a bit technical, but the important thing is that my company's future.

1044
02:05:57,050 --> 02:05:57,710
Right, Mr. Fox?

1045
02:05:58,330 --> 02:05:59,410
Right you are, Mr. Wayne.

1046
02:06:02,550 --> 02:06:03,470
Didn't you get the memo?

1047
02:06:04,130 --> 02:06:24,680
I didn't tell you, Rachel.

1048
02:06:24,680 --> 02:06:27,010
No, no, Bruce. I'm sorry.

1049
02:06:28,670 --> 02:06:34,410
The day that Chell died, I... I said terrible things.

1050
02:06:35,390 --> 02:06:36,010
But true things.

1051
02:06:37,840 --> 02:06:39,180
I was a coward with a gun.

1052
02:06:39,720 --> 02:06:43,260
Justice is about more than revenge, so thank you.

1053
02:06:44,240 --> 02:06:46,330
I never stopped thinking about you.

1054
02:06:48,850 --> 02:06:49,350
About us.

1055
02:06:50,050 --> 02:06:54,890
When I heard you were back, I started to hope.

1056
02:07:20,280 --> 02:07:21,820
Then I found out about your mask.

1057
02:07:34,130 --> 02:07:36,840
Your real face is the one that criminals now fear.

1058
02:07:38,490 --> 02:07:39,230
A man I loved.

1059
02:07:41,030 --> 02:07:41,810
A man who vanished.

1060
02:07:43,830 --> 02:07:44,950
He never came back at all.

1061
02:08:12,990 --> 02:08:13,990
Proved me wrong, you know.

1062
02:08:14,550 --> 02:08:14,870
About what?

1063
02:08:18,670 --> 02:08:20,130
Father would be very proud of you.

1064
02:08:21,360 --> 02:08:22,000
Just like me.

1065
02:08:50,010 --> 02:08:50,630
What will you do?

1066
02:08:53,250 --> 02:08:53,770
Rebuild it?

1067
02:08:55,670 --> 02:08:57,190
Just the way it was, brick for brick.

1068
02:09:04,900 --> 02:09:05,920
Just the way it was, sir?

1069
02:09:08,360 --> 02:09:08,760
Yeah, why?

1070
02:09:09,660 --> 02:09:13,760
I thought this might be a good opportunity for, uh, improving the foundations.

1071
02:09:15,280 --> 02:09:16,360
In the southeast corner?

1072
02:09:17,360 --> 02:09:18,120
Precisely, sir.

1073
02:09:35,160 --> 02:09:36,580
I couldn't find any mob bosses.

1074
02:09:37,440 --> 02:09:38,450
Well, Sergeant?

1075
02:09:38,910 --> 02:09:41,790
Oh, it's Lieutenant now. He really started something.

1076
02:09:42,550 --> 02:09:45,650
Bent cops running scared. Hope on the streets.

1077
02:09:46,310 --> 02:09:46,510
But?

1078
02:09:46,550 --> 02:09:48,710
The Narrows is lost.

1079
02:09:50,470 --> 02:09:53,810
And we still haven't picked up Crane or half the inmates of Arkham that he freed.

1080
02:09:54,930 --> 02:09:57,610
We will. We can recover.

1081
02:09:58,570 --> 02:09:59,550
What about Escalation?

1082
02:10:00,030 --> 02:10:00,550
Escalation?

1083
02:10:01,250 --> 02:10:04,710
When we start carrying semi-automatics, they buy automatics.

1084
02:10:05,730 --> 02:10:09,690
When we start wearing Kevlar, they buy armor-piercing rounds.

1085
02:10:10,370 --> 02:10:10,630
And?

1086
02:10:10,670 --> 02:10:15,560
And you're wearing a mask, jumping off rooftops.

1087
02:10:17,180 --> 02:10:18,020
I take this guy.

1088
02:10:19,620 --> 02:10:21,000
Armed robbery, double homicide.

1089
02:10:21,800 --> 02:10:24,780
Had a taste for the theatrical, like you.

1090
02:10:25,360 --> 02:10:26,280
Leaves a calling card.

1091
02:10:38,390 --> 02:10:39,550
I never said thank you.

